    "title": "Heart pump maker Abiomed settles U.S. kickback probe for $3.1 mln",
    "locations": [],
    "highlightText": "",
    "language": "english",
    "persons": [],
    "text": "BOSTON, March 8 (Reuters) - Abiomed Inc has agreed to pay $3.1 million to resolve a U.S. investigation into allegations that it sought to induce doctors into using a line of heart pumps it produced by buying them lavish meals.\nThe civil settlement was announced on Thursday by U.S. Attorney Andrew Lelling in Massachusetts and resolves allegations first raised in a whistleblower lawsuit filed by a former Abiomed employee. (Reporting by Nate Raymond in Boston Editing by Chizu Nomiyama)\nOur Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles.",
